getPackageName().Description: The package name of the source of this event.

getClassName().Description: The class name of the source of this event. This may be null for certain events.

Returns: the standby bucket associated with the event.
getAppStandbyBucket().Description: Returns the standby bucket of the app, if the event is of type @B_android#app#usage#UsageEvents#Event#STANDBY_BUCKET_CHANGED_E@, otherwise returns 0.

getTimeStamp().Description: The time at which this event occurred, measured in milliseconds since the epoch. See @B_java#lang#System#currentTimeMillis_E@.

getConfiguration().Description: Returns a @B_android#content#res#Configuration_E@ for this event if the event is of type @B_android#app#usage#UsageEvents#Event#CONFIGURATION_CHANGE_E@, otherwise it returns null.

getShortcutId().Description: Returns the ID of a @B_android#content#pm#ShortcutInfo_E@ for this event if the event is of type @B_android#app#usage#UsageEvents#Event#SHORTCUT_INVOCATION_E@, otherwise it returns null.

ClassDesc: An event representing a state change for a component.
